056/**
057 * A {@link Constable}, immutable, sorted set of key-value pairs that
058 * can be used to further qualify an object for many different
059 * purposes.
060 *
061 * <p>Keys are sorted according to their natural order.</p>
062 *
063 * <p>This is a <a
064 * href="https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/doc-files/ValueBased.html">value-based
065 * class</a>.</p>
066 *
067 * <p>Values of type {@code K} must be members of classes adhering to
068 * <a
069 * href="https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/doc-files/ValueBased.html">value-based
070 * semantics</a>.</p>
071 *
072 * <p>Values of type {@code V} must be members of classes adhering to
073 * <a
074 * href="https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/doc-files/ValueBased.html">value-based
075 * semantics</a>.</p>
076 *
077 * <p>Undefined behavior will result if the preceding requirements are
078 * not honored.</p>
079 *
080 * @param <K> the type borne by the keys of the qualifiers in this
081 * {@link Qualifiers}
082 *
083 * @param <V> the type borne by the values of the qualifiers in this
084 * {@link Qualifiers}
085 *
086 * @author <a href="https://about.me/lairdnelson"
087 * target="_parent">Laird Nelson</a>
088 *
089 * @see #of(Constable, Constable)
090 */
091public final class Qualifiers<K extends Constable & Comparable<K>, V extends Constable> implements Constable, Iterable<Entry<K, V>> {
092
093

095   * Static fields.
096   */
097

115  /**
116   * Creates a new {@linkplain Map#isEmpty() empty} {@link
117   * Qualifiers}.
118   */
119  public Qualifiers() {
120    this(Map.of(), false);
121  }
122
123  /**
124   * Creates a new {@link Qualifiers}.
125   *
126   * @param qualifiers a {@link Map} representing the qualifiers; may be
127   * {@code null} in which case an {@linkplain Map#isEmpty() empty
128   * <code>Map</code>} will be used instead
129   */
130  public Qualifiers(final Map<? extends K, ? extends V> qualifiers) {
131    this(qualifiers, true);
132  }
133
134  @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
135  private Qualifiers(final Map<? extends K, ? extends V> qualifiers, final boolean copy) {
136    if (qualifiers == null || qualifiers.isEmpty()) {
137      this.qualifiers = emptySortedMap();
138    } else if (copy || !(qualifiers instanceof SortedMap)) {
139      this.qualifiers = unmodifiableSortedMap(new TreeMap<>(qualifiers));
140    } else {
141      this.qualifiers = unmodifiableSortedMap((SortedMap<K, V>)qualifiers);
142    }
143  }

257  /**
258   * Returns {@code true} if this {@link Qualifiers} logically
259   * contains the supplied {@link Qualifiers}.
260   *
261   * <p>A {@link Qualifiers} is said to contain another {@link
262   * Qualifiers} if either:</p>
263   *
264   * <ul>
265   *
266   * <li>the two {@link Qualifiers} instances are identical, or</li>
267   *
268   * <li>the {@linkplain Map#size() size} of the first {@link Qualifiers}
269   * is greater than the {@linkplain Map#size() size} of the second
270   * {@link Qualifiers}, and the {@linkplain Map#entrySet() entry set}
271   * of this {@link Qualifiers} {@linkplain
272   * Set#containsAll(java.util.Collection) contains all} of the
273   * entries in the second {@link Qualifiers}' {@linkplain
274   * Map#entrySet() entry set}</li>
275   *
276   * </ul>
277   *
278   * @param other the {@link Qualifiers} to test; must not be {@code
279   * null}
280   *
281   * @return {@code true} if this {@link Qualifiers} logically
282   * contains the supplied {@link Qualifiers}
283   *
284   * @exception NullPointerException if {@code other} is {@code null}
285   *
286   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
287   *
288   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
289   * threads.
290   *
291   * @see Map#size()
292   *
293   * @see Set#containsAll(java.util.Collection)
294   */
295  public final boolean contains(final Qualifiers<?, ?> other) {
296    return this == other || this.size() >= other.size() && this.toMap().entrySet().containsAll(other.toMap().entrySet());
297  }
298
299  /**
300   * Returns {@code true} if and only if this {@link Qualifiers}
301   * logically contains an entry equal to the supplied {@link Entry}.
302   *
303   * @param e the {@link Entry} to test; may be {@code null} in which
304   * case {@code false} will be returned
305   *
306   * @return {@code true} if and only if this {@link Qualifiers}
307   * logically contains an entry equal to the supplied {@link Entry}
308   *
309   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
310   *
311   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
312   * threads.
313   */
314  public final boolean contains(final Entry<?, ?> e) {
315    final Object v = e == null ? null : this.toMap().get(e.getKey());
316    return v != null && v.equals(e.getValue());
317  }

359  /**
360   * Returns {@code true} if and only if this {@link Qualifiers} is a
361   * subset of the supplied {@link Qualifiers}.
362   *
363   * @param other the other {@link Qualifiers}; must not be {@code
364   * null}
365   *
366   * @return {@code true} if and only if this {@link Qualifiers} is a
367   * subset of the supplied {@link Qualifiers}
368   *
369   * @exception NullPointerException if {@code other} is {@code null}
370   *
371   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
372   *
373   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
374   * threads.

376  public final boolean isSubsetOf(final Qualifiers<?, ?> other) {
377    return other == this || other.contains(this);
378  }

380  /**
381   * Returns the number of entries this {@link Qualifiers} has in
382   * common with the supplied {@link Qualifiers}.
383   *
384   * <p>The number returned will be {@code 0} or greater.</p>
385   *
386   * @param other the other {@link Qualifiers}; may be {@code null} in
387   * which case {@code 0} will be returned
388   *
389   * @return the number of entries this {@link Qualifiers} has in
390   * common with the supplied {@link Qualifiers}
391   *
392   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
393   *
394   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
395   * threads.
396   */
397  public final int intersectionSize(final Qualifiers<?, ?> other) {
398    if (other == this) {
399      // Just an identity check to rule this easy case out.
400      return this.size();
401    } else if (other == null || other.isEmpty()) {
402      return 0;
403    } else {
404      final Collection<? extends Entry<?, ?>> otherEntrySet = other.toMap().entrySet();
405      return (int)this.toMap().entrySet()
406        .stream()
407        .filter(otherEntrySet::contains)
408        .count();
409    }
410  }
411
412  /**
413   * Returns the size of the <em>symmetric difference</em> between
414   * this {@link Qualifiers} and the supplied {@link Qualifiers}.
415   *
416   * <p>The number returned is always {@code 0} or greater.</p>
417   *
418   * <p>The size of the symmetric difference between two {@link
419   * Qualifiers} instances is the number of qualifier entries that are
420   * in one {@link Qualifiers} instance but not in the other.</p>
421   *
422   * @param other the other {@link Qualifiers} instance; may be {@code
423   * null}
424   *
425   * @return the size of the <em>symmetric difference</em> between
426   * this {@link Qualifiers} and the supplied {@link Qualifiers};
427   * always {@code 0} or greater
428   *
429   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
430   *
431   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
432   * threads.
433   */
434  public final int symmetricDifferenceSize(final Qualifiers<?, ?> other) {
435    if (other == this) {
436      // Just an identity check to rule this easy case out.
437      return 0;
438    } else if (other == null || other.isEmpty()) {
439      return this.size();
440    } else if (this.equals(other)) {
441      return 0;
442    } else {
443      final Collection<Entry<?, ?>> otherSymmetricDifference = new HashSet<>(this.toMap().entrySet());
444      other.toMap()
445        .entrySet()
446        .stream()
447        .filter(Predicate.not(otherSymmetricDifference::add))
448        .forEach(otherSymmetricDifference::remove);
449      return otherSymmetricDifference.size();
450    }
451  }

453  /**
454   * Returns an {@link Optional} containing a {@link ConstantDesc}
455   * representing this {@link Qualifiers}.
456   *
457   * @return an {@link Optional} containing a {@link ConstantDesc}
458   * representing this {@link Qualifiers}; never {@code null}; never
459   * {@linkplain Optional#isEmpty() empty}
460   *
461   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
462   *
463   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
464   *
465   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
466   * threads.
467   */
468  @Override // Constable
469  public final Optional<? extends ConstantDesc> describeConstable() {
470    final Collection<Entry<K, V>> entrySet = this.toMap().entrySet();
471    if (entrySet.isEmpty()) {
472      return
473        Optional.of(DynamicConstantDesc.ofNamed(BSM_INVOKE,
474                                                DEFAULT_NAME,
475                                                CD_Qualifiers,
476                                                MethodHandleDesc.ofMethod(STATIC,
477                                                                          CD_Qualifiers,
478                                                                          "of",
479                                                                          MethodTypeDesc.of(CD_Qualifiers))));
480    } else {
481      final int bsmInvokeArgumentsLength = 2 * entrySet.size() + 1;
482      final ConstantDesc[] bsmInvokeArguments = new ConstantDesc[bsmInvokeArgumentsLength];
483      bsmInvokeArguments[0] =
484        MethodHandleDesc.ofMethod(STATIC,
485                                  CD_Qualifiers,
486                                  "of",
487                                  MethodTypeDesc.of(CD_Qualifiers,
488                                                    CD_Constable.arrayType()));
489      int i = 1;
490      for (final Entry<K, V> entry : entrySet) {
491        final Constable key = entry.getKey();
492        final ConstantDesc k = key == null ? null : key.describeConstable().orElse(null);
493        if (k == null) {
494          return Optional.empty();
495        }
496        bsmInvokeArguments[i++] = k;
497        final Constable value = entry.getValue();
498        final ConstantDesc v = value == null ? NULL : value.describeConstable().orElse(null);
499        if (v == null) {
500          return Optional.empty();
501        }
502        bsmInvokeArguments[i++] = v;
503      }
504      return Optional.of(DynamicConstantDesc.ofNamed(BSM_INVOKE,
505                                                     DEFAULT_NAME,
506                                                     CD_Qualifiers,
507                                                     bsmInvokeArguments));
508    }
509  }

528  /**
529   * Returns {@code true} if this {@link Qualifiers} is equal to the
530   * supplied {@link Object}.
531   *
532   * @param other the object to test; may be {@code null} in which
533   * case {@code false} will be returned
534   *
535   * @return {@code true} if this {@link Qualifiers} is equal to the
536   * supplied {@link Object}; {@code false} otherwise
537   *
538   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
539   *
540   * @threadsafety This method is safe  for concurrent use by multiple
541   * threads.
542   */
543  @Override // Object
544  public final boolean equals(final Object other) {
545    if (other == this) {
546      return true;
547    } else if (other != null && other.getClass() == this.getClass()) {
548      final Qualifiers<?, ?> her = (Qualifiers<?, ?>)other;
549      return
550        Objects.equals(this.toMap(), her.toMap());
551    } else {
552      return false;
553    }
554  }

575  /**
576   * Returns a <strong>usually new</strong> {@link Qualifiers} whose
577   * keys are produced by the supplied {@link Function}, which is
578   * expected to prepend a prefix to the original key and return the
579   * result.
580   *
581   * <p>If this {@link Qualifiers} is {@linkplain #isEmpty() empty},
582   * then {@code this} is returned.</p>
583   *
584   * @param f a deterministic, idempotent {@link Function} that
585   * accepts keys drawn from this {@link Qualifiers}' {@linkplain
586   * Map#entrySet() entry set} and returns a non-{@code null} prefixed
587   * version of that key; may be {@code null} in which case {@code
588   * this} will be returned
589   *
590   * @return a <strong>usually new</strong> {@link Qualifiers} whose
591   * keys have been prefixed by the actions of the supplied {@link
592   * Function}
593   *
594   * @exception NullPointerException if {@code f} is {@code null}
595   *
596   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
597   *
598   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic,
599   * assuming the supplied {@link Function} is.
600   *
601   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
602   * threads, assuming the supplied {@link Function} is
603   */
604  public final Qualifiers<K, V> withPrefix(final Function<? super K, ? extends K> f) {
605    if (f == null || this.isEmpty()) {
606      return this;
607    } else {
608      final Map<K, V> map = new TreeMap<>();
609      for (final Entry<? extends K, ? extends V> entry : this.toMap().entrySet()) {
610        map.put(f.apply(entry.getKey()), entry.getValue());
611      }
612      return new Qualifiers<>(map, false);
613    }
614  }

616  /**
617   * Returns a {@link Qualifiers} with additional
618   * entries sourced from the supplied {@link Qualifiers}.
619   *
620   * <p>The returned {@link Qualifiers} <strong>will be new</strong>
621   * unless {@code qualifiers} is {@code null} or {@linkplain
622   * #isEmpty() empty}, in which case {@code this} will be
623   * returned.</p>
624   *
625   * @param qualifiers a {@link Qualifiers} whose entries will be part
626   * of the new {@link Qualifiers}, displacing any that already exist;
627   * may be {@code null} or {@linkplain Map#isEmpty() empty} in which
628   * case {@code this} will be returned; all keys and values must be
629   * immutable (not just unmodifiable) or undefined behavior will
630   * result
631   *
632   * @return a {@link Qualifiers} with additional entries sourced from
633   * the supplied {@link Qualifiers}; never {@code null}
634   *
635   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
636   *
637   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
638   *
639   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
640   * threads.
641   *
642   * @see #plus(Map)
643   */
644  public final Qualifiers<K, V> plus(final Qualifiers<? extends K, ? extends V> qualifiers) {
645    if (qualifiers == null || qualifiers.isEmpty()) {
646      return this;
647    } else {
648      return this.plus(qualifiers.toMap());
649    }
650  }
651
652  /**
653   * Returns a {@link Qualifiers} with additional
654   * entries sourced from the supplied {@link Map}.
655   *
656   * <p>The returned {@link Qualifiers} <strong>will be new</strong>
657   * unless {@code qualifiers} is {@code null} or {@linkplain
658   * Map#isEmpty() empty}, in which case {@code this} will be
659   * returned.</p>
660   *
661   * @param qualifiers a {@link Map} whose entries will be part of the
662   * new {@link Qualifiers}, displacing any that already exist; may be
663   * {@code null} or {@linkplain Map#isEmpty() empty} in which case
664   * {@code this} will be returned; all keys and values must be
665   * immutable (not just unmodifiable) or undefined behavior will
666   * result
667   *
668   * @return a {@link Qualifiers} with additional entries sourced from
669   * the supplied {@link Map}; never {@code null}
670   *
671   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
672   *
673   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
674   *
675   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
676   * threads.
677   */
678  public final Qualifiers<K, V> plus(final Map<? extends K, ? extends V> qualifiers) {
679    if (qualifiers == null || qualifiers.isEmpty()) {
680      return this;
681    } else {
682      final Map<K, V> map = new TreeMap<>(this.toMap());
683      map.putAll(qualifiers);
684      return new Qualifiers<>(map, false);
685    }
686  }

688  /**
689   * Returns an immutable {@link Map} representation of this {@link
690   * Qualifiers}.
691   *
692   * @return an immutable {@link Map} representation of this {@link
693   * Qualifiers}
694   *
695   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
696   *
697   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
698   *
699   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
700   * threads.
701   */
702  public final Map<K, V> toMap() {
703    return this.qualifiers;
704  }

717   * {@link Qualifiers} will be empty)

721   * {@link Qualifiers} will be empty)

732  // Used by #describeConstable()
733  @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
734  public static final <K extends Constable & Comparable<K>, V extends Constable> Qualifiers<K, V> of() {
735    return (Qualifiers<K, V>)EMPTY_QUALIFIERS;
736  }

740   * entries represented by the supplied {@link Map}.
741   *

743   * returned {@link Qualifiers}
744   *
745   * @param <V> the type borne by the values of the qualifiers in the
746   * returned {@link Qualifiers}
747   *
748   * @param map the {@link Map} of qualifier names and values; may be
749   * {@code null} in which case the return value of the {@link #of()}
750   * method will be returned

753   * entries represented by the supplied {@link Map}
754   *
755   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
756   *
757   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
758   *
759   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
760   * threads.
761   *
762   * @see #of(Constable, Constable)
763   */
764  @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
765  public static final <K extends Constable & Comparable<K>, V extends Constable> Qualifiers<K, V> of(final Map<? extends K, ? extends V> map) {

882  /**
883   * Returns a {@link Qualifiers} consisting of the entries
884   * represented by the supplied alternating name-value pairs.
885   *
886   * <p>The supplied {@code nameValuePairs} must be an even-numbered
887   * array of non-{@code null} {@link Constable} instances, where the
888   * zero-based even-numbered elements are {@link String}s represents
889   * qualifier names, and the zero-based odd-numbered {@link
890   * Constable} elements represent qualifier values.</p>
891   *
892   * @param <K> the type borne by the keys of the qualifiers in the
893   * returned {@link Qualifiers}
894   *
895   * @param <V> the type borne by the values of the qualifiers in the
896   * returned {@link Qualifiers}
897   *
898   * @param nameValuePairs the name-value pairs as described above;
899   * may be {@code null} in which case the return value of the {@link
900   * #of()} method will be returned
901   *
902   * @return a {@link Qualifiers} consisting of the entries
903   * represented by the supplied alternating name-value pairs
904   *
905   * @exception IllegalArgumentException if an even number of
906   * arguments is not supplied
907   *
908   * @exception ClassCastException if elements in the supplied array
909   * at even positions ({@code 0}, {@code 2}, {@code 4}…) are not of
910   * type {@code K}
911   *
912   * @exception NullPointerException if any argument is {@code null}
913   *
914   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
915   *
916   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
917   *
918   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
919   * threads.
920   */
921  // Used by #describeConstable()
922  @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
923  public static final <K extends Constable & Comparable<K>, V extends Constable> Qualifiers<K, V> of(final Constable... nameValuePairs) {
924    if (nameValuePairs == null || nameValuePairs.length <= 0) {
925      return of();
926    } else if (nameValuePairs.length % 2 != 0) {
927      throw new IllegalArgumentException("nameValuePairs: " + Arrays.toString(nameValuePairs));
928    } else {
929      final Map<K, V> map = new TreeMap<>();
930      for (int i = 0; i < nameValuePairs.length; i++) {
931        map.put((K)nameValuePairs[i++], (V)nameValuePairs[i]);
932      }
933      return new Qualifiers<>(map);
934    }
935  }
